full_text: @CarlDunnJr A shock, unexpected news or trigger seemingly coming out of nowhere makes my brain immediately detach it can be hard to come back depending on what happened but strong smells and enjoyable sensations help if those don't work I have to wait it out
full_text(utf-8): b"@CarlDunnJr A shock, unexpected news or trigger seemingly coming out of nowhere makes my brain immediately detach it can be hard to come back depending on what happened but strong smells and enjoyable sensations help if those don't work I have to wait it out"

full_text: @CarlDunnJr Scents like lavender, a warm cup of tea or cool bath. Use things that you enjoy and try to focus on soaking up the smell, weight, temperature etc. I find photography helps me as it makes me want to be present and focus on my surroundings
full_text(utf-8): b'@CarlDunnJr Scents like lavender, a warm cup of tea or cool bath. Use things that you enjoy and try to focus on soaking up the smell, weight, temperature etc. I find photography helps me as it makes me want to be present and focus on my surroundings'

full_text: @CarlDunnJr Sometimes but even when I do remember the memories are hazy and there's a sense that it wasn't me experiencing those things
full_text(utf-8): b"@CarlDunnJr Sometimes but even when I do remember the memories are hazy and there's a sense that it wasn't me experiencing those things"

full_text: @CarlDunnJr It has caused problems such as one time I got hit by a car because I was so detached from my surroundings. There's also chunks of my life I can't remember so I feel like theres pieces missing to the puzzle that makes up me/my life.
full_text(utf-8): b"@CarlDunnJr It has caused problems such as one time I got hit by a car because I was so detached from my surroundings. There's also chunks of my life I can't remember so I feel like theres pieces missing to the puzzle that makes up me/my life."

full_text: @CarlDunnJr It usually happens when something has triggered me. I think it's not necessarily away for me to detach from the trigger but the strong emotional reactions that come from the trigger such as fear and anger. It helps soften the impact of those emotions on me
full_text(utf-8): b"@CarlDunnJr It usually happens when something has triggered me. I think it's not necessarily away for me to detach from the trigger but the strong emotional reactions that come from the trigger such as fear and anger. It helps soften the impact of those emotions on me"

full_text: Mental illness is an ongoing thing. With battles that go on far beyond this week or month. We still face stigma everyday especially if you have something like BPD. Mental health needs to be talked about everyday in order to truly be seen as normal and not just once a year
full_text(utf-8): b'Mental illness is an ongoing thing. With battles that go on far beyond this week or month. We still face stigma everyday especially if you have something like BPD. Mental health needs to be talked about everyday in order to truly be seen as normal and not just once a year'

full_text: Like me feel like crap for not getting better or "over it" sooner. It's good for friends to check in on us but don't get people to expect a drastic improvement in our wellbeing, it can help but we can go down again. We need to teach people to be patient with us
full_text(utf-8): b'Like me feel like crap for not getting better or "over it" sooner. It\'s good for friends to check in on us but don\'t get people to expect a drastic improvement in our wellbeing, it can help but we can go down again. We need to teach people to be patient with us'

full_text: No ribbon to wrap it all up nearly. You can overcome it. You can prgoress. But it takes time, trial and error. There is no quick fix. I like to believe in the cause and ending of stigma but please normalise long term mental illness struggles as it can make people
full_text(utf-8): b'No ribbon to wrap it all up nearly. You can overcome it. You can prgoress. But it takes time, trial and error. There is no quick fix. I like to believe in the cause and ending of stigma but please normalise long term mental illness struggles as it can make people'

full_text: Recovery from mental illness is not linear. Talking with friends and family can help but it requires a lot of our own strength and determination to get up and try again. Like mentioned in turtles all the way down there's no neat ending to a fight with mental illness
full_text(utf-8): b"Recovery from mental illness is not linear. Talking with friends and family can help but it requires a lot of our own strength and determination to get up and try again. Like mentioned in turtles all the way down there's no neat ending to a fight with mental illness"

full_text: Talking our way over it, it takes a lot of unlearning and relearning. A lot of falling and getting back up again. Many losses, relapses. Many times you may think you "got over" something for something to happen to make you have to confront it again. That's normal
full_text(utf-8): b'Talking our way over it, it takes a lot of unlearning and relearning. A lot of falling and getting back up again. Many losses, relapses. Many times you may think you "got over" something for something to happen to make you have to confront it again. That\'s normal'

full_text: Not mean my battle is over. If you are still fighting, I'm proud of you and it's okay to not have found the "cure" I like the sentiment of mental health awareness but it sort of portrays mental illness as a short term thing when it often is long term and there's no
full_text(utf-8): b'Not mean my battle is over. If you are still fighting, I\'m proud of you and it\'s okay to not have found the "cure" I like the sentiment of mental health awareness but it sort of portrays mental illness as a short term thing when it often is long term and there\'s no'

full_text: Issues don't work like that and I understand people want to give the message of hope that we can recover and get better it sort of makes me feel guilty for not feeling much better after years of fighting. I'm pleased to say that I have made progress but that does
full_text(utf-8): b"Issues don't work like that and I understand people want to give the message of hope that we can recover and get better it sort of makes me feel guilty for not feeling much better after years of fighting. I'm pleased to say that I have made progress but that does"

full_text: Long story short you never know how close you could come to tragedy. I might do something in the girl's memory idk but may she rest in peace (9/9) https://t.co/0oY65JOBbs
full_text(utf-8): b"Long story short you never know how close you could come to tragedy. I might do something in the girl's memory idk but may she rest in peace (9/9) https://t.co/0oY65JOBbs"

full_text: Not far from where they found her body and where the tragedy struck. I remember the dread I felt seeing that helicopter and the shock of finding out what happened later. I was 9 at the time and it's one of the few things I can almost clearly recall now (8/9)
full_text(utf-8): b"Not far from where they found her body and where the tragedy struck. I remember the dread I felt seeing that helicopter and the shock of finding out what happened later. I was 9 at the time and it's one of the few things I can almost clearly recall now (8/9)"

full_text: Details of the story from the news on that day, like the rubber dinghy and the man who tried to save her and her friend. I remember the phase the news used "got into trouble in the water" I looked it up and found an article about it. It haunts me to think I was (7/9)
full_text(utf-8): b'Details of the story from the news on that day, like the rubber dinghy and the man who tried to save her and her friend. I remember the phase the news used "got into trouble in the water" I looked it up and found an article about it. It haunts me to think I was (7/9)'

full_text: Friends and family still affected by this. You could just as easily be one of those people involved in such a tragedy. I may have simply been a bystander to that girl's death but remembering it now still affects me greatly. Just that feeling of dread and I can recall (6/9)
full_text(utf-8): b"Friends and family still affected by this. You could just as easily be one of those people involved in such a tragedy. I may have simply been a bystander to that girl's death but remembering it now still affects me greatly. Just that feeling of dread and I can recall (6/9)"

full_text: Like I said I am interested in mysteries and conspiracies but it's important to remember that while elements of the story added by others may be fiction at the heart of the story is the truth and that person had a life before their tragedy and that they have/had (5/9)
full_text(utf-8): b"Like I said I am interested in mysteries and conspiracies but it's important to remember that while elements of the story added by others may be fiction at the heart of the story is the truth and that person had a life before their tragedy and that they have/had (5/9)"

full_text: Sensationalising them with conspiracy theories and elaborating with our imagination to sort of take a step back from the brutal reality that these aren't characters and this isn't a game to figure out what happened it's a real event with real people involved (4/9)
full_text(utf-8): b"Sensationalising them with conspiracy theories and elaborating with our imagination to sort of take a step back from the brutal reality that these aren't characters and this isn't a game to figure out what happened it's a real event with real people involved (4/9)"

full_text: By such tragedies. I will always have a fascination with ghosts and unsolved mysteries but it's important to remember that in these "stories" were real people who died horrific deaths. I think we sort of don't want to accept the reality of these things and start (3/9)
full_text(utf-8): b'By such tragedies. I will always have a fascination with ghosts and unsolved mysteries but it\'s important to remember that in these "stories" were real people who died horrific deaths. I think we sort of don\'t want to accept the reality of these things and start (3/9)'

full_text: And later on I found out that a girl not much older than I was had drowned in that sea and the helicopter I saw had been searching for her body. I forgot about it until today and it just makes me realise how real these things are and how easily it could be us affected (2/9)

full_text: I didn't stick to the plan of running until I could do a marathon this month but I am more active than I was a month ago by using the stairs and dancing my hyperactivity away. Overall it's small changes but better than nothing and for now I leave you with this picture ‚ô•Ô∏è https://t.co/LsnmhLgw5p
full_text(utf-8): b"I didn't stick to the plan of running until I could do a marathon this month but I am more active than I was a month ago by using the stairs and dancing my hyperactivity away. Overall it's small changes but better than nothing and for now I leave you with this picture \xe2\x99\xa5\xef\xb8\x8f https://t.co/LsnmhLgw5p"

full_text: My main goal was to be more active, sleep and eat better. Well like I said my sleep is scarce but for a while I was able to balance my sleep so at least I know I can do it. Still eat a lot of junk food but I have started snacking more on fruit and veg than crisps and chocolate
full_text(utf-8): b'My main goal was to be more active, sleep and eat better. Well like I said my sleep is scarce but for a while I was able to balance my sleep so at least I know I can do it. Still eat a lot of junk food but I have started snacking more on fruit and veg than crisps and chocolate'

full_text: And eat healthily all the time, I used building mastery to make small changes such as taking the stairs instead of the lift and introducing more fruit and veg to my diet in small amounts. It wasn't much but it was something
full_text(utf-8): b"And eat healthily all the time, I used building mastery to make small changes such as taking the stairs instead of the lift and introducing more fruit and veg to my diet in small amounts. It wasn't much but it was something"

full_text: Goal setting and coming up with steps for them definitely isn't my strong point, I found it difficult to write a plan on how I wanted to do things but the point of building mastery is to push yourself a little bit each day. Even though I couldn't go for runs every morning
full_text(utf-8): b"Goal setting and coming up with steps for them definitely isn't my strong point, I found it difficult to write a plan on how I wanted to do things but the point of building mastery is to push yourself a little bit each day. Even though I couldn't go for runs every morning"

full_text: Which meant I had less energy to excersise more but thanks to hyperactivity I went for a run at 4am one time and started dancing in the middle of the night as I was too wired to sleep so that's a plus. I completed worksheets and journal ex for values and building mastery
full_text(utf-8): b"Which meant I had less energy to excersise more but thanks to hyperactivity I went for a run at 4am one time and started dancing in the middle of the night as I was too wired to sleep so that's a plus. I completed worksheets and journal ex for values and building mastery"

full_text: As sometimes things didn't go to plan. For a couple of weeks I got into a sleep routine and was able to be up at a certain time every morning but then I had my medication increased which seemed to cause hyperactivity in me so I started getting less sleep
full_text(utf-8): b"As sometimes things didn't go to plan. For a couple of weeks I got into a sleep routine and was able to be up at a certain time every morning but then I had my medication increased which seemed to cause hyperactivity in me so I started getting less sleep"

full_text: I used values to decide what I wanted to focus on first, then building mastery to help me achieve my goals and PLEASE because I wanted to improve my diet, sleep and exercise more. I had to keep readjusting my expectations of myself and coming up with new steps
full_text(utf-8): b'I used values to decide what I wanted to focus on first, then building mastery to help me achieve my goals and PLEASE because I wanted to improve my diet, sleep and exercise more. I had to keep readjusting my expectations of myself and coming up with new steps'
